The log you posted is truncated before the actual error. Right now it only shows the compilation command, not the reason the build failed.

Also, there are two separate issues:

1. Qt could not connect to display

You're running virtualbox as root from a terminal without an X11 display.

If this is a headless server, use:

VBoxManage --version

instead of virtualbox.

Or launch it from a graphical desktop as a normal user.



2. Kernel module build failed (this is the real problem)

vboxdrv was not built for your kernel:

5.14.0-611.26.1.el9_7.x86_64




First, check these packages

uname -r

rpm -q kernel-devel-$(uname -r)
rpm -q kernel-headers-$(uname -r)
rpm -q gcc
rpm -q make
rpm -q elfutils-libelf-devel

If any package is missing:

dnf install gcc make perl elfutils-libelf-devel kernel-devel-$(uname -r) kernel-headers-$(uname -r)

Then run:

/sbin/vboxconfig


---

Next, find the real error

Run:

tail -100 /var/log/vbox-setup.log

or

grep -i "error" /var/log/vbox-setup.log

The last 50-100 lines contain the actual compilation failure.


---

Check Secure Boot

mokutil --sb-state

If it returns:

SecureBoot enabled

then the VirtualBox kernel modules must be signed, or Secure Boot must be disabled.


---

Check VirtualBox version

VBoxManage --version

Older VirtualBox versions (6.x or early 7.x) often do not support RHEL 9.7 kernel 5.14.0-611.


---

Please send the output of these commands:

tail -50 /var/log/vbox-setup.log

VBoxManage --version

uname -r

rpm -q kernel-devel-$(uname -r)

The last 50 lines of /var/log/vbox-setup.log will identify the exact cause.
